  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to add a new mailserver so that I can make sure it isn't blocked.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4299\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: An adversary can easily block mailserver IPs and our users won't be able to communicate. To prevent this users should be able to specify their own mailserver addresses.\r\n\r\nSimilar to https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4264\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nA user can specify their own mailserver\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nOnly Status mailservers can be selected\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nStatus already has an Advanced setting called \"offline messages\". We can extend this to include adding new mail servers.\r\n\r\nThe design pattern should follow https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4239\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n\r\n- Change copy \"Offline messages\" to \"Mailserver\" in advanced settings, and on the settings screen\r\n- Add a âž• icon to the mailserver listing screen\r\n- Based on the work done in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/4239, add a new screen with `name` and `address` fields.\r\n- Add categories to the mailserver list page with headings \"Status mailservers\", and when a user has added one show \"Custom mailservers\"\r\n- Custom mailservers can be tapped with a detail screen showing a connect button, field to edit the address, and a delete button.",
